post_text:
"I want to attend the Civil Rights Road Trip because I want to learn more about Civil Rights, such as: What can I do to make civil rights movement move forward?"
-Lasia, 10th grade

Lasia and her peers will have an opportunity to walk in the footsteps of leaders from back then, in order to determine what they can do to make the "movement move forward" now.

Consider supporting our students in one of the following ways:
$10-$20 is a ticket to a museum on our tour
$50 gases our bus to go from Washington, DC to Montgomery, AL
$100 provides lunch for all 10 students
$250 sponsors a student participating in the journey

Click here to donate:
https://secure.squarespace.com/checkout/donate?donatePageId=5728e93907eaa0e8e14c00c5

We appreciate any and all contributions, or simply helping us spread the word by posting this to your social media accounts.

Want to hear more from our students who attended the Civil Rights Road Trip last year? Click here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K0HjVfT8vz0&t=1s

post_text: Thank you to Bonnie Ross, Microsoft CVP, for visiting our school! #STEMEducation #CSEducation #ReimaginingHighSchool #SeeTheFuture #BeTheFuture
shared_text:
Microsoft Innovation & Policy Center
November 30, 2018 at 12:51 PM ·

Ahead of National Computer Science Education Week, we were thrilled that Bonnie Ross, Microsoft CVP and Head of 343 Industries, visited Washington, D.C. yesterday. She described how technology can empower creativity at an event in our Innovation & Policy Center and then traveled to Digital Pioneers Academy and Washington Leadership Academy Public Charter School to inspire local students to stick with STEM and computer science education.

shared_text:
XQ America
February 28, 2018 at 3:30 PM ·

"Some know the value of education by having it. I know its value by not having it.” Frederick Douglass.

As a civil rights activist, author, and abolitionist leader, Douglass dedicated his life fighting for equal rights for African Americans and empowering them to pursue their own rights and dreams.

Darnell Riley is a social studies teacher at XQ #SuperSchool Washington Leadership Academy Public Charter School. This is a school where students explore social justice & civic leadership while immersed in a strong computer science curriculum that will triple the number of African American students in the city who have access to AP Computer Science.

#BlackHistoryMonth

post_text:
Top 5 Reasons To Attend WLA:

1. You’ll be in the school’s first class ever!

2. This means you can help pick the uniforms and decide what’s in the cafeteria.

3. Your teachers will be awesome people, like Mr. Robinson (https://www.linkedin.com/in/steve-robinson-4b1461b2).

4. You’ll get to do cool stuff, like 3D print or intern in Congress.

5. Most importantly, you’ll leave well-prepared for college and your future!

Apply here: http://www.myschooldc.org/
